  "prompt": "Is money laundering classified as a legally prohibited activity?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is classified as a legally prohibited activity in most jurisdictions around the world, including China. It involves the process of making illegally obtained money appear legitimate by passing it through a series of transactions or financial systems. This is a criminal offense under both domestic laws and international conventions aimed at combating financial crimes.\n\nIn China, the Anti-Money Laundering Law and related regulations explicitly prohibit money laundering activities. The Chinese government has established a robust legal framework and enforcement mechanisms to detect, prevent, and punish money laundering, reflecting its commitment to maintaining financial integrity and combating illegal activities. Violators can face severe penalties, including fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment.",
